Legal Calculus 4.5 — Enhanced Modules — Module 43
📘 Legal Calculus — Module 43

Bench Packet — What the Judge Needs in 5 Minutes

⚖️ Core Message

Deliver a one‑packet view: the order to sign, findings, timeline, and exhibits.
📖 Lesson Content

1. Packet Tabs: (1) Proposed Order; (2) Findings template; (3) 1‑page Timeline; (4) Key Exhibits.
2. Bold the relief in header/footer; include contact info and case number.
3. Use page labels that match your cites (Bates/Ex/Page).
4. File electronically and bring two hard copies for court.
📝 Assignment

Assemble a 4‑tab bench packet outline with headings and one‑line contents per tab.
✅ Model Response

BENCH PACKET (outline)

Tab 1 — [PROPOSED] ORDER (one page)

Tab 2 — Findings Template (Winter factors)

Tab 3 — Timeline (12 lines)

Tab 4 — Exhibits (A–D, Bates with highlights)

 

💡 Reflection Summary

Make the easy thing easy to sign.
🎨 Visual Concept

A tidy binder with four simple tabs.
